{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17639826","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17639826"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:10:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:10:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17789"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17789"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.9,0,0.05,0,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10503"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75823"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10503","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10503"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17789"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61336"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1091"},{"type":"tags","id":"1184"},{"type":"tags","id":"1713"},{"type":"tags","id":"3521"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5884"},{"type":"tags","id":"10948"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24509"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24514"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75823","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75823"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-month history of amenorrhea and galactorrhea. She is of childbearing age but has been experiencing infertility. Pregnancy tests have been negative. She also reports progressive headaches and has noticed some visual disturbances. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Visual field testing reveals bitemporal hemianopia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pituitary adenoma","Hypothyroidism","Polycystic ovary syndrome","Hyperprolactinemia due to medication","Craniopharyngioma"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s symptoms of amenorrhea, galactorrhea, and bitemporal hemianopia are suggestive of a \u003Cstrong\u003Epituitary adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E, specifically a prolactinoma. Prolactin-secreting pituitary adenomas are the most common type of functioning pituitary tumor and can lead to hyperprolactinemia, causing galactorrhea and amenorrhea. The bitemporal hemianopia is due to compression of the optic chiasm by the enlarging tumor.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause menstrual irregularities and galactorrhea, but it would not cause bitemporal hemianopia or headaches related to mass effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolycystic ovary syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E can cause amenorrhea and infertility but does not cause galactorrhea or visual field defects.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHyperprolactinemia due to medication\u003C/strong\u003E (such as antipsychotics) can cause galactorrhea and amenorrhea, but would not cause bitemporal hemianopia or headaches from mass effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECraniopharyngioma\u003C/strong\u003E can cause visual disturbances and headaches due to its location near the optic chiasm, but it is less likely to cause galactorrhea and amenorrhea compared to a prolactinoma.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A pituitary adenoma can cause amenorrhea, galactorrhea, and bitemporal hemianopia due to compression of the optic chiasm.","Prolactin-secreting pituitary adenomas (prolactinomas) are a common cause of hyperprolactinemia, leading to galactorrhea and amenorrhea.","Bitemporal hemianopia is a sign of mass effect from a pituitary tumor compressing the optic chiasm."],"references":["Russ S, Anastasopoulou C, Shafiq I. Pituitary Adenoma. 2023 Mar 27. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32119338.","Markou M, Lavrentaki A, Ntali G. Recent advances in understanding and managing pituitary adenomas. Fac Rev. 2023 Mar 21;12:6. doi: 10.12703/r/12-6. PMID: 36968144; PMCID: PMC10032474.","Banskota S, Adamson DC. Pituitary Adenomas: From Diagnosis to Therapeutics. Biomedicines. 2021 Apr 30;9(5):494. doi: 10.3390/biomedicines9050494. PMID: 33946142; PMCID: PMC8146984."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61336"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17789"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61336"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-31T17:17:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T17:17:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10503"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75823"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"8","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/8"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc41","name":"Ophthalmology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"posi